<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <key>Label</key>
  <string>com.jleechan.mcp-daemon</string>

  <key>ProgramArguments</key>
  <array>
    <string>/bin/bash</string>
    <string>@HOME@/.config/mcp-daemon/start-mcp-daemons.sh</string>
    <string>start</string>
  </array>

  <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
  <dict>
    <key>PATH</key>
    <string>@HOME@/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.0/bin:@HOME@/bin:/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/sbin</string>
    <key>HOME</key>
    <string>@HOME@</string>
  </dict>

  <!--
    Self-healing supervisor. The start-mcp-daemons.sh script wraps each
    MCP server in a `while true; do npx supergateway ...; sleep 3; done`
    bash loop, so the script itself exits quickly after spawning those
    loops. KeepAlive + ThrottleInterval makes launchd respawn the script
    within 60s if it ever dies (e.g. SIGTERM, OOM, manual kill), without
    flooding the system.

    Why not just StartInterval=300? 2026-06-17 incident: launchd silently
    entered `state = not running, active count = 0` after a clean
    RunAtLoad — the StartInterval schedule stopped firing with no error
    in any log. KeepAlive is the durable insurance against that class
    of supervisor death. ThrottleInterval caps the respawn rate.

    See: feedback_2026-06-17_mcp_daemon_diagnosis_fixes (bead rev-gu8bi)
    See: ~/.claude/projects/-Users-jleechan-projects-worldarchitect-ai/memory/feedback_2026-06-17_mcp_daemon_diagnosis_fixes.md
  -->
  <key>KeepAlive</key>
  <true/>

  <key>ThrottleInterval</key>
  <integer>60</integer>

  <!--
    Periodic reconcile: every 5 minutes, re-run the script. Each
    supergateway is wrapped in its own restart loop inside the script,
    so this is belt-and-suspenders for the case where a bash loop
    itself was killed.
  -->
  <key>StartInterval</key>
  <integer>300</integer>

  <key>RunAtLoad</key>
  <true/>

  <key>StandardOutPath</key>
  <string>@HOME@/.config/mcp-daemon/logs/launchd.log</string>
  <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
  <string>@HOME@/.config/mcp-daemon/logs/launchd.log</string>
</dict>
</plist>
